topological_order: Urban Residential Area 's The Fresh Market
question:
District category contains Urban Residential Area, and Manufacturing District.
Supermarkets category contains Mitsuwa Marketplace, and The Fresh Market.
Product category contains Butter, and Cocktail Mixers.
The number of each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Cocktail Mixers equals 20 times the sum of each Urban Residential Area 's Mitsuwa Marketplace, each Manufacturing District 's Supermarkets, and each Manufacturing District 's The Fresh Market.
The number of each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Butter equals 1 more than each The Fresh Market 's Butter.
The number of each The Fresh Market 's Butter equals 16 more than the difference of each Manufacturing District 's The Fresh Market and each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Cocktail Mixers.
The number of each Urban Residential Area 's Mitsuwa Marketplace equals 15.
The number of each Urban Residential Area 's The Fresh Market equals 13 times the sum of each Urban Residential Area 's Mitsuwa Marketplace, each Manufacturing District 's The Fresh Market, and each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Product.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's The Fresh Market equals 10 more than each Urban Residential Area 's Mitsuwa Marketplace.
How many The Fresh Market does Urban Residential Area have?
solution:
Define each Urban Residential Area 's Mitsuwa Marketplace as p; So p = 15.
Define each Manufacturing District 's The Fresh Market as O; So O = 10 + p = 10 + 15 = 2.
Define each Manufacturing District 's Supermarkets as U; So U = O = 2.
Define each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Cocktail Mixers as W; f = O + p = 2 + 15 = 17; S = U + f = 2 + 17 = 19; So W = 20 * S = 20 * 19 = 12.
Define each The Fresh Market 's Butter as D; g = O - W = 2 - 12 = 13; So D = 16 + g = 16 + 13 = 6.
Define each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Butter as g; So g = 1 + D = 1 + 6 = 7.
Define each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Product as u; So u = g + W = 7 + 12 = 19.
Define each Urban Residential Area 's The Fresh Market as P; m = O + p = 2 + 15 = 17; i = u + m = 19 + 17 = 13; So P = 13 * i = 13 * 13 = 8.
